text: The Shaki-Zagatala economic-geographical region is one of ten regions in Azerbaijan. The region includes Sheki, Zagatala, Balakan, Oghuz, Gakh and Gabala administrative districts. It borders Dagestan, Russia, in the north, Georgia (at the Mazim River) to the west, and the Girdiman Valley to the east and south. ==Related pages== *Economic regions of Azerbaijan
title: Shaki-Zagatala Economic Region
